    "content": "The following algorithm computes the integral $$\\,J = \\int\\limits_a^b {f\\left( x \\right)dx\\,\\,\\,} $$ from the given values $${f_j} = f\\left( {{x_j}} \\right)$$ at equidistant points $$\\,\\,{x_0} = a,\\,\\,{x_1} = {x_0} + h,\\,\\,$$ $$\\,{x_2} = {x_0} + 2h,...\\,{x_{2m}} = {x_0} + 2mh = b\\,\\,$$ compute\n<br>$${S_0} = {f_0} + {f_{2m}}$$\n<br>$${S_1} = {f_1} + {f_3} + .... + {f_{2m - 1}}$$\n<br>$${S_2} = {f_2} + {f_4} + .... + {f_{2m - 2}}$$ \n<p><b>$$J = {h \\over 3}\\left[ {{S_0} + 4\\left( {{S_1}} \\right) + 2\\left( {{S_2}} \\right)} \\right]$$</b></p>\n<p>The rule of numerical integration, which uses the above algorithm is </p>",
